&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.transform(parser)
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.filter(Predicates.notNull())
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;.copyInto(returnCollection);
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return returnCollection;
}

For something involving Maps, this becomes even more awkward to implement. 

Given that the Joiner class itself is final, and its Strategy is a private class, and given that there's no way to define a Splitter (or Joiner) with a parameterized Strategy, the same way you can create custom implementations of Multimap/Table with a parameterized Supplier, how hard would it to be to make Splitter&lt;E> with DefaultSplitter implementing Splitter&lt;String>, and adding (lazy pseudocode example):

public &lt;T> Splitter.TransformingSplitter&lt;T> withTransform(Function&lt;String, T> transform){
