}

TransformingSplitter&lt;T>{
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Splitter&lt;String> originalSplitter
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Function&lt;String, T> function;

```
public <G> TransformingSplitter<T> withTransform(Function<T,G> transform){
    return new TransformingSplitter<G>(this, Functions.compose(transform, function);
}

//Implement the transformingIterator
```

}

Similar for MapSplitter, being able to transform element types in the map returned would be most helpful.

How feasible would it be for Splitter to be genericized so that by default it splits into a collection&lt;String> or Map&lt;String,String> but can in turn split into Collection&lt;Integer>, Map&lt;Integer,POJO>, etc?

How feasible would it also be to create a Splitter.splitInto(String unsplit, Collection&lt;T> copyInto) void method? Similar to how Joiner has Joiner.appendTo, Splitter.splitInto would be helpful for assorted functions. 

