System.out.println(b1.isAssignableFrom(b0));

I would expect all of these comparisons to return true, but the first instead prints false. In the first case (b0) the byte[] type is represented internally as an instance of GenericArrayTypeImpl. The equals() on GenericArrayTypeImpl will only attempt a comparison to other GenericArrayType subclasses. I believe this equals method should also handle comparison to non-generic array types when appropriate.
